# Retrieve Security Images

### Introduction

If a user tries to log in without a configured pin code, the [authentication endpoint](../../authentication/) will alert them that they need to configure a pin code first. To configure a pin code, it is also necessary to select an image from a predefined image set using this endpoint.

{% swagger method="get" path="/v{apiVersion}/assets/security-images" baseUrl="baseURL" summary="Returns the set of security images for pin codes" %}
{% swagger-description %}

{% endswagger-description %}

{% swagger-parameter in="path" name="apiVersion" type="String" required="true" %}
Version of the API. By default, set it to 1.0
{% endswagger-parameter %}

{% swagger-parameter in="header" name="Authorization" type="String" required="true" %}
This is the authorization token from the very first token request. The value of this header must have the following format: 

`Bearer BQ898r9fefi`

 (

`Bearer`

 \+ 1 space + the token).
